						               													<description>Traffic USA is the exciting reality board game of driving in the United States of America.  If is fun, informative and engaging.  Traffic USA is a game for both young and old, that the entire family will enjoy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the Game:&amp;#10;The object of the game is to be the first player to travel from &amp;quot;START HERE&amp;quot; to &amp;quot;FINISH HERE&amp;quot; by completing a trip around the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play:&amp;#10;There are three kinds of play: (A) Single Play - one round trip; (B) Double Play - two round trips; (C) Triple Play - three round trips.  Players must choose a game play before the start of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(1) Each player chooses one car token and gets $1,000.00 play money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(2) Each player rolls the die to see who plays first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(3) If two players roll the same number, both must roll again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(4) The player that rolls the highest &amp;quot;mph&amp;quot; plays first.  Play continues from left to right, so that the person sitting to the left of player #1 becomes players #2 and so on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(5) To start the game, player #1 rolls the die and moves forward in the direction of the green arrow the number of miles rolled on the die.  For example, if player #1 rolls &amp;quot;10 mph&amp;quot; on the die, he or she moves forward two spaces (each space equals five miles).  If player #2 rolls &amp;quot;25 mph&amp;quot;, he or she moves forward five spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(6) When a player lands on a space with a traffic sign, he or she must obey the sign as instructed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(7) When a player lands on a space with a store or business, he or she can buy the store or business for the purchase price on the deed card.  If another player already owns the business, then the player must pay the owner the revenue as stated on the deed card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(8) Play continues as players take turns playing and obeying all traffic rules and regulations along the route from &amp;quot;START HERE&amp;quot; to &amp;quot;FINISH HERE&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winning the game:&amp;#10;The player to reach &amp;quot;FINISH HERE&amp;quot; first after completing a trip around the board wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
